usdoj/jmd/css/mam


   The Attorney General, as head of the Department of Justice and chief
   law enforcement officer of the Federal Government, represents the
   United States in legal matters generally and gives advice and opinions
   to the President and to the heads of the executive departments of the
   Government when so requested. The Attorney General appears in person to
   represent the Government before the U.S. Supreme Court in cases of
   exceptional gravity or importance.

                       Attorney General John Ashcroft
                              Attorney General
                                John Ashcroft

